OL,3,CWorkers putting in billions of pounds
OL,4,Cof unpaid overtime ` report
OL,6,FThe TUC said its study indicated that
OL,7,F3.8 million people worked unpaid
OL,8,Fovertime in 2024, putting in an
OL,9,Faverage of 7.2 unpaid hours a week,
OL,10,Fequivalent to an average to #8,000 a
OL,11,Fyear of lost wages.
OL,13,FLondon had the highest proportion of
OL,14,Fworkers doing unpaid overtime, at 17%,
OL,15,Fcompared to 13% nationally, while
OL,16,Foccupations with most unpaid overtime
OL,17,Fwere teaching and health and care
OL,18,Fmanagers, which the TUC said
OL,19,Fhighlighted staffing pressures in
OL,20,Fschools and hospitals.
