OL,6,F"It is really important the new
OL,7,Fgovernment engages with its workforce
OL,8,Fon issues like workloads to stop staff
OL,9,Fleaving our schools and hospitals.
OL,11,F"We are encouraging every worker to
OL,12,Ftake their lunchbreak and finish on
OL,13,Ftime today, and we know that good
OL,14,Femployers will support them doing
OL,15,Fthat."
OL,17,FRuth Wilkinson, head of policy at the
OL,18,FInstitution of Occupational Safety and
OL,19,FHealth, said: "It's concerning that
OL,20,Fpeople are working so many additional
OL,21,Fhours, especially without pay.
