OL,6,F"This 'always-on' culture not only
OL,7,Fblurs the boundaries between work and
OL,8,Fhome life, it impacts on people's
OL,9,Fopportunities to have sufficient rest,
OL,10,Fsomething which is potentially harmful
OL,11,Fas it can cause burnout and other
OL,12,Fhealth and safety issues.
OL,14,F"The knock-on effect of this is more
OL,15,Fpeople being on sick leave."
